  "bezeichnung": "Sustainability Impact Assessment",
  "kreditpunkte": 3,
  "lernziele": "<p>Over the past century, our consumption and production have created problems we must solve for a sustainable future. Old methods no longer work&mdash;innovation is key. Measuring impact is crucial to assess solutions, refine approaches, and avoid unintended effects. It ensures transparency, builds trust, and secures support. This seminar explores the link between innovation and sustainability, focusing on impact assessment. With startups and experts from the One Planet Lab (a WWF innovation hub), you will analyze solutions, present findings, and reflect critically. Join to bridge theory and practice, develop new strategies, and drive real change toward a sustainable future!&nbsp;</p>",
  "semesterBewertung": "Note von 1 - 6",
